Privacy Policy – Quba App

Effective Date: 16 October 2025

Quba (“we”, “our”, or “us”) respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use the Quba mobile application.


---

1. Information We Collect

Student Data: Name, roll number, subjects, and marks (entered manually by the user)

Device Information: Android version, device model, app version (automatically collected)

Optional Sharing: Any PDFs you choose to share via email, WhatsApp, or other apps


> ⚠️ Note: Quba does not collect or transmit any personal information to our servers. All data remains on your device.




---

2. How We Use Your Information

To generate student result PDFs

To calculate totals, percentages, and grades

To allow saving and sharing of PDFs



---

3. Data Storage

All data is stored locally on your device.

No cloud storage or third-party servers are used by default.



---

4. Sharing of Information

The app does not share your data with third parties.

Any sharing of PDFs is done manually by the user through standard Android sharing options.



---

5. Third-Party Services

Quba does not integrate any analytics or advertising services.



---

6. Security

We implement basic security practices to ensure your data is safe on your device.

Users are responsible for device-level security (lock screen, backups, etc.).



---

7. Changes to Privacy Policy

We may update this policy occasionally.

Any changes will be reflected on the same GitHub URL.



---

8. Contact Us

For any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
Email: support@qubaapp.com (optional)
GitHub: https://github.com/yourusername/quba-privacy
